The FASN synthase inhibitor cerulenin has been shown to reduce production of several viruses such as VV, WNV, and Semliki Forest virus (
 Martin-Acebes et al., 2011; 
 Greseth and Traktman, 2014; 
 Royle et al., 2017), suggesting that 
 de novo fatty acid biosynthesis is relevant for numerous viral infections.
